From f1b78f608beb515298eb31efa3943603dcb506a5 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <claude@anthropic.local>
Date: Sun, 19 Jul 2026 07:18:22 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Manager 1-1 performance reviews (Phase 1) and fix merge
 regressions
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

Design fixes: restore the summary page display heading lost in the merge,
retire the last legacy palette hex, and convert remaining inline layout
styles on summary/settings into the design system.

Manager 1-1s: migration 011 creates managers (records, not logins),
one_to_one_reviews with the eight-area scoring model, and a master action
log whose items carry forward between reviews instead of disappearing.
All writes go through security-definer RPCs with audit logging; finalised
reviews lock, snapshot their KPIs, require development notes for scores
below 3 and owners/dates on every agreed action, and can be reopened only
with a recorded reason. Managers acknowledge finalised reviews.

The KPI section re-types nothing: sales, GP, labour, waste, stock basis
and report status pull straight from the kitchen's existing weekly report
snapshot; only audit score and compliance are recorded in the meeting,
with corrective action required for amber/red compliance.

Centralised scoring service covers score RAG, overall and dashboard
category averages, higher/lower-is-better KPI variance in the correct
units, zero-target safety, probation stages, weighted probation scores,
overdue action detection and the follow-up email builder — 15 new unit
tests. Seed script adds Scott Hutton and Warren Raisbeck with their agreed
focus actions.
